.TH MOOR 1 "March 2026" "MOOR 0.7.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
moor \- post-quantum anonymous overlay network
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B moor
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
MOOR routes traffic through 3 encrypted hops using X25519 + Kyber768 hybrid
key exchange. No single relay knows both source and destination. Every hop
is post-quantum resistant.
.PP
With no arguments, MOOR starts as a SOCKS5 proxy client on port 9050.
.SH MODES
.TP
.B Client (default)
SOCKS5 proxy on localhost. Route browser/application traffic through the network.
.TP
.B \-\-mode relay
Onion relay. Forwards encrypted cells between other nodes.
.TP
.B \-\-mode da
Directory authority. Publishes signed consensus of known relays.
.TP
.B \-\-mode hs
Hidden service. Host a service reachable via .moor addresses.
.TP
.B \-\-mode ob
OnionBalance. Load-balance a hidden service across multiple backends.
.TP
.B \-\-mode bridgedb
Bridge distribution service. Hands out bridge addresses via HTTPS.
.TP
.B \-\-mode bridge_auth
Bridge authority. Publishes a separate consensus of bridge relays.
.SH CLIENT OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-socks\-port \fIport\fR
SOCKS5 listen port (default: 9050).
.TP
.B \-\-bind \fIaddr\fR
Bind address (default: 127.0.0.1).
.TP
.B \-\-da\-address \fIaddr\fR
Primary directory authority address (default: 107.174.70.38).
.TP
.B \-\-da\-port \fIport\fR
Primary directory authority port (default: 9030).
.TP
.B \-\-use\-bridges
Connect via bridge relays instead of direct.
.TP
.B \-\-bridge \fIline\fR
Bridge specification: "transport addr:port pk_hex".
.TP
.B \-\-geoip \fIfile\fR
IPv4 GeoIP database for path diversity (Tor format).
.TP
.B \-\-geoip6 \fIfile\fR
IPv6 GeoIP database for path diversity (Tor format).
.TP
.B \-\-conflux
Enable multi-path circuits.
.TP
.B \-\-conflux\-legs \fIn\fR
Number of circuit legs (default: 2).
.TP
.B \-\-padding\-machine \fIname\fR
WTF-PAD machine: web, stream, generic, none (default: generic).
.TP
.B \-\-pir / \-\-no\-pir
Enable/disable PIR for hidden service lookups (default: on).
.TP
.B \-\-data\-dir \fIdir\fR
Persistent state directory (guards, consensus cache).
.SH RELAY OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-or\-port \fIport\fR
Onion routing port (default: 9001).
.TP
.B \-\-guard
Advertise as guard relay (entry point for client circuits). Under 20 relays
in the network, the DA trusts this flag immediately. Over 20, the relay must
earn it via Fast + Stable + bandwidth + 8 days uptime.
.TP
.B \-\-exit
Advertise as exit relay (forwards traffic to the internet). Always self-declared,
never auto-assigned. Nobody accidentally becomes an exit.
.TP
.B \-\-middle\-only
Middle-only relay. DA strips Guard/Exit/HSDir flags. Safest to run.
.TP
.B \-\-advertise \fIaddr\fR
Public IP to advertise (auto-detected if omitted).
.TP
.B \-\-nickname \fIname\fR
Human-readable relay name (shows in consensus).
.TP
.B \-\-bandwidth \fIbytes/s\fR
Advertised bandwidth (default: 1000000). DA measures actual throughput.
.TP
.B \-\-is\-bridge
Run as unlisted bridge relay (not published in consensus).
.TP
.B \-\-bridge\-transport \fItype\fR
Bridge transport: scramble, shade, mirage (default: scramble).
.TP
.B \-\-mix\-delay \fIms\fR
Poisson mixing delay in milliseconds (0 = disabled).
.TP
.B \-\-pow\-difficulty \fIn\fR
Argon2id PoW difficulty for relay registration (default: 8).
.TP
.B \-\-pow\-memlimit \fIKB\fR
Argon2id memory limit (default: 256).
.SH DA OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-dir\-port \fIport\fR
Directory service port (default: 9030).
.TP
.B \-\-da\-peers \fIlist\fR
Peer DAs: ip:port or ip:port:hex_identity_pk, comma-separated.
.SH HS OPTIONS
Hidden services require a config file:
.PP
.RS
.nf
Mode hs
DAAddress 107.174.70.38
DAPort 9030
HiddenServiceDir /path/to/keys
HiddenServicePort 8080
.fi
.RE
.PP
The .moor address is printed on first run and derived from the service key.
.SH TRANSPARENT PROXY OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-TransPort \fIport\fR
Transparent TCP proxy port (redirect traffic without SOCKS).
.TP
.B \-\-DNSPort \fIport\fR
Transparent DNS port (resolve through the network).
.SH ADVANCED OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-f, \-\-config \fIfile\fR
Load configuration from file. See moorrc.sample for all options.
.TP
.B \-\-control\-port \fIport\fR
Tor-compatible control port for monitoring (0 = disabled).
.TP
.B \-\-monitor
Enable runtime statistics logging.
.TP
.B \-\-daemon
Fork to background.
.TP
.B \-\-pid\-file \fIpath\fR
Write PID file (implies --daemon).
.TP
.B \-v
Verbose logging.
.SH RELAY TYPES
With no role flags, a relay is a general-purpose relay. The directory authority
assigns Guard/Exit based on performance metrics. Under 20 relays in the network,
self-declared flags are trusted immediately. Over 20:
.PP
.RS
.B Fast
\- bandwidth >= 12.5th percentile
.br
.B Stable
\- uptime >= median
.br
.B Guard
\- Fast + Stable + bandwidth + 8 days uptime
.br
.B HSDir
\- Fast + Stable + 96 hours uptime
.br
.B Exit
\- always self-declared (--exit flag)
.RE
.PP
Nobody accidentally becomes an exit relay. Exit is always opt-in.
.SH CRYPTO
All key exchanges use X25519 + Kyber768 (ML-KEM-768) hybrid.
Consensus is dual-signed with Ed25519 + ML-DSA-65 (Dilithium3).
Link handshakes use Noise_IK with BLAKE2b and ChaCha20-Poly1305.
Post-quantum is mandatory and cannot be disabled.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Run as client:
.B moor
.TP
Browse via MOOR:
.B curl -x socks5h://127.0.0.1:9050 http://example.com
.TP
Run a middle relay:
.B moor --mode relay --advertise 1.2.3.4 --nickname MyRelay -v
.TP
Run an exit relay:
.B moor --mode relay --exit --advertise 1.2.3.4 --nickname MyExit -v
.TP
Run a guard relay:
.B moor --mode relay --guard --advertise 1.2.3.4 --nickname MyGuard -v
.TP
Run DA with trusted peer:
.B moor --mode da --da-peers 1.2.3.4:9030:abcdef...
.TP
Run via bridge:
.B moor --use-bridges --bridge "scramble 1.2.3.4:443 abcdef..."
.TP
Easy relay setup:
.B curl -sL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/0xdeadbeefnetwork/MOOR_PQ/main/setup.sh | sudo bash
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.moor/
Default data directory (guards, consensus cache, keys).
.TP
.I moorrc.sample
Example configuration file with all options documented.
.TP
.I /etc/moor/moor.conf
System-wide configuration (created by setup.sh).
.SH SEE ALSO
Full documentation: https://moor.afflicted.sh/docs.html
.PP
GitHub: https://github.com/0xdeadbeefnetwork/MOOR_PQ
